Here is a corrected version of your code:

```tundra
val groups = [
  {
    name: "north",
    entries: [
      { amount: 2 },
      { amount: 3 }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: "south",
    entries: [
      { amount: 4 }
    ]
  }
];

var total = 0;
for (group in groups) {
  for (entry in group.entries) {
    total = total + entry.amount;
  }
}

print(total);
```
This version will sum up the 'amount' values from each nested object within
within the 'entries' lists, and then print out this summed total. It should
should now return 9 as expected.
